<div class="d d-r">
<div class="s">Who should not use muscle-growth peptides</div>
<p>Individuals with active cancer or recent history of malignancy (all these compounds promote cell growth). Diabetics or pre-diabetics (GH antagonizes insulin). People with active cardiovascular disease (fluid shifts, blood pressure effects). Pregnant or nursing women. Competitive athletes subject to WADA testing (all listed GH secretagogues and IGF-1 are prohibited at all times). Anyone under 25 whose growth plates have not fully closed (GH/IGF-1 can cause acromegaly-like changes).</p>
</div>

